deck: Mexican publication from the sixties and seventies
description: Published in the early sixties by Editormex Mexicana, this blackly horror coic series ran for many years. At first the publication was called 'Brujerias' which is Spanish for Witchcraft. The Mexican Public Education Department insisted that the publisher change the weekly's title because it promoted superstition.The comic then got named after the head witch in the stories called Hermelinda Linda, which stands for 'Pretty Hermelinda".
name: Brujerias

description:
From the artist and writer team behind the web comic Jonbot vs. Martha.

Dungeon Fun is the story of a girl and her sword…

Raised by trolls in the moat of a castle, Fun Mudlifter lives a life of boredom, until one day when adventure finds her and a sword plummets into her village. Setting off to confront the trolls responsible for the falling items that plague her and her neighbors, Fun begins an off-beat odyssey that encompasses jobsworth trolls, three-headed beasts, soothsaying shamans and headless barbarians, as she valiantly battles her way up through the dungeons to her final goal. With hilarious results!
name: Dungeon Fun
